is Saruman the white.

448
00:50:52,085 --> 00:50:54,841
Then there are the two druidses.

449
00:50:55,930 --> 00:50:59,651
And the other
i quite forgotten their names.

450
00:50:59,820 --> 00:51:04,800
And who is the fifth?
- That would be, Radagast the Brown.

451
00:51:04,964 --> 00:51:08,685
Is he a great wizard
or Is he...more like you?

452
00:51:10,777 --> 00:51:15,502
I think he is a very great wizard.
In his own way.

453
00:51:15,671 --> 00:51:20,315
He is a gentle soul, who prefers
the company of animals to others.

454
00:51:20,481 --> 00:51:24,876
He keeps a watchful eye
over the vast forest land, to the East.

455
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:31,189
And a good thing too, for always evil
will look to find foothold in this world.

456
00:51:37,487 --> 00:51:41,310
Not good.
Not at all good.

457
00:52:05,692 --> 00:52:08,161
No, Sebastian.

458
00:52:11,541 --> 00:52:13,842
Good gracious.

459
00:52:34,378 --> 00:52:37,558
Move back.
Give him some air! For goodness sake...

460
00:52:50,178 --> 00:52:53,202
I don't understand why it's not working.

461
00:52:53,359 --> 00:52:55,662
As if it's witchcraft.

462
00:52:58,418 --> 00:53:01,330
Witchcraft ...

463
00:53:02,063 --> 00:53:06,078
Oh, but it is.

464
00:53:06,954 --> 00:53:12,851
A dark and powerful magic.

465
00:54:44,780 --> 00:54:49,706
Where on this good earth
did does foul creatures come from?

466
00:54:51,133 --> 00:54:55,934
The old forest?
Show me.

467
00:55:28,645 --> 00:55:32,947
We camp here for the night.
Fili.. Kili, look after the ponies.

468
00:55:32,948 --> 00:55:35,478
Make sure you stay with them.

469
00:55:35,552 --> 00:55:39,508
Farmer and his family
must've lived here.

470
00:55:39,544 --> 00:55:42,989
Oin, Gloin, get a fire going.

471
00:55:43,713 --> 00:55:46,569
I think it would be wiser,
to move on.

472
00:55:48,221 --> 00:55:51,562
We could make to the hidden Valley drive.

473
00:55:51,725 --> 00:55:55,493
I told you, already.
I will not go near that place.

474
00:55:55,528 --> 00:56:00,029
Why not? The Elves can help us.
We could get food, rest... advice.

475
00:56:00,198 --> 00:56:02,199
I do not need their advice.

476
00:56:02,370 --> 00:56:06,296
We have a map, that we cannot read.
Lord Elrond could help us.

477
00:56:06,331 --> 00:56:08,952
Help?

478
00:56:09,119 --> 00:56:13,665
When the Dragons attacked, Erebor
what help came from the Elves?

479
00:56:14,541 --> 00:56:19,125
Orcs plundered Moria
and desecrated our Sacred halls.

480
00:56:19,295 --> 00:56:23,088
The Elves looked on and did nothing.

481
00:56:23,253 --> 00:56:28,506
You ask me to seek out the very people
who betrayed my granfather, betrayed my father?

482
00:56:28,747 --> 00:56:30,828
You're neither of them.

483
00:56:30,829 --> 00:56:34,857
I did not give you that map and key
for you, to hold on to the past.

484
00:56:34,960 --> 00:56:38,380
I did not know, nobody ought to keep.

485
00:56:42,532 --> 00:56:45,883
Everything alright?
Gandalf, where are you going?

486
00:56:46,052 --> 00:56:49,589
To seek the company of the only one around here
who's got any sense.

487
00:56:49,624 --> 00:56:52,389
And who is that?
-Myself, Mr. Baggins.

488
00:56:52,558 --> 00:56:57,058
I've had enough of dwarfs for one day.

489
00:56:57,228 --> 00:57:02,769
C'mon, Bombur. We are hunger.
-Is he coming back?

490
00:57:05,570 --> 00:57:11,402
He'd been a long time..Gandalf.
- He's a wizard. He does what he chooses.

491
00:57:11,569 --> 00:57:16,947
Here, do us a favor.
Take this to the lads.

492
00:57:35,667 --> 00:57:38,876
What's the matter?
- We're suppose to be looking after the ponies.

493
00:57:39,045 --> 00:57:43,297
Only we've encountered a slight problem.
-We had 16.

494
00:57:43,467 --> 00:57:49,138
Now there is.. 14.

495
00:57:50,053 --> 00:57:54,514
Daisy and Bungo are missing.
-Well, that is not good.

496
00:57:54,679 --> 00:57:58,098
And that is not good at all.
-Shouldn'd we tell Thorin?

497
00:57:58,267 --> 00:58:02,343
Ahh no, let's not worry him.
As our official burglar

498
00:58:02,344 --> 00:58:04,611
we thought,
you might want to look into it.

499
00:58:04,646 --> 00:58:09,399
Well, look something big
uprooted these trees.

500
00:58:09,568 --> 00:58:14,571
That was our thinking.
-Something very big and possibly quite dangerous.

501
00:58:15,652 --> 00:58:19,237
Hey, There is a light.

502
00:58:19,405 --> 00:58:22,616
Over Here.

503
00:58:23,160 --> 00:58:25,783
Stay down.

504
00:58:29,702 --> 00:58:34,540
What is it?
- Trolls.

505
00:59:02,807 --> 00:59:07,521
We have to do something.
-Yes, you should.

506
00:59:07,686 --> 00:59:11,813
Mountain trolls are slow and stupid,
and you're so small they will never see you.

507
00:59:11,977 --> 00:59:13,980
It is perfectly safe.
We'll be right behind you.

508
00:59:14,148 --> 00:59:17,974
If you run into trouble, hoot twice like a bowl owl..
and once like a brawl owl.

509
00:59:18,009 --> 00:59:22,944
Twice like a bowl owl..once like a brawl owl..
Are you sure this is a good idea?

510
00:59:23,531 --> 00:59:27,947
Mutton yesterday.
Mutton today..and like.

511
00:59:28,116 --> 00:59:33,160
And it all look like mutton again tomorrow.
-quit your groaning.

512
00:59:33,329 --> 00:59:38,209
These ain't sheep.
These's fresh maine.

513
00:59:38,372 --> 00:59:43,291
I don't like horses. I never have...
not enough fat on 'em.

514
00:59:43,461 --> 00:59:45,903
But better than that livery old farmer.

515
00:59:45,939 --> 00:59:51,296
All skin and bone he was.
I'm still thinkin' he's bit in me teeth.

516
00:59:51,466 --> 00:59:56,758
That's lovely taste..a floater.
-Oh, does improve the flavour.

517
00:59:56,926 --> 01:00:02,556
Oh, more where that came from.
-Oh, no you don't.

518
01:00:04,682 --> 01:00:08,228
Sit down.

519
01:00:15,275 --> 01:00:21,293
You haven't kept these nags.
-But I like the stinky parts.

520
01:00:23,119 --> 01:00:25,583
I said, Sit down.

521
01:00:25,751 --> 01:00:29,669
I'm starving.
Are we gonna eat that horse or not?

522
01:00:29,834 --> 01:00:33,866
Shut your Cakcom.
You eat what i give ya.

523
01:00:34,671 --> 01:00:38,255
Bert is the Cook
Everything tastes the same.

524
01:00:38,590 --> 01:00:43,006
Everything tastes like chicken.
-Except the chicken. That taste like fish.

525
01:00:43,042 --> 01:00:48,596
I'm just saying
a little appreciatio would be nice.

526
01:00:49,636 --> 01:00:54,707
' Thank you Very much Bert'
' Lovely stew, Bert '. How hard is that?

527
01:00:56,975 --> 01:01:01,391
Just need a sprinkle of squirrel there .

528
01:01:01,560 --> 01:01:03,642
That's my grog.

529
01:01:05,273 --> 01:01:08,191
Sorry.

530
01:01:11,193 --> 01:01:14,883
That is beautifully balanced.
That is.

531
01:01:15,715 --> 01:01:21,119
Let me know if it need any else.
Good, in'it?

532
01:01:23,514 --> 01:01:26,671
That's how I cook.

533
01:01:33,953 --> 01:01:38,192
Me gags are rumbling.
I've got to snack something.

534
01:01:38,359 --> 01:01:41,144
Flesh, I need flesh.

535
01:01:44,677 --> 01:01:48,367
Bert..Look what's come outta me otter.

536
01:01:48,512 --> 01:01:52,338
It 's got arms and legs and everything.
-What is it?

537
01:01:52,501 --> 01:01:55,747
I don't know,
but i don't like the way it's wriggling.

538
01:01:58,987 --> 01:02:02,396
What are you then?
An oversized squirrel?

539
01:02:02,560 --> 01:02:06,467
I'm a burglar. A Hobbit.
-A burglar hobbit?

540
01:02:06,634 --> 01:02:11,745
Can we cook him?
-We can try.

541
01:02:13,702 --> 01:02:18,688
He might be more than a mouthful,
not only skin and bone.

542
01:02:18,856 --> 01:02:24,634
There's more hobbit in this part.
More than enough for a pie.

543
01:02:25,546 --> 01:02:28,370
Get him.
- Its too quick.

544
01:02:29,327 --> 01:02:32,400
Oh you little,..
Gotcha.

545
01:02:32,567 --> 01:02:36,415
Are there anymore of you little fellas hiding
where you shouldn't?

546
01:02:36,416 --> 01:02:37,416
No.

547
01:02:38,221 --> 01:02:41,089
He is lying.
-I'm not.

548
01:02:41,253 --> 01:02:46,449
Hold his toes over  the fire,
Make him squeel.

549
01:02:50,314 --> 01:02:52,934
Drop him!
-You want...what?

550
01:02:53,099 --> 01:02:57,505
I said, Drop him!

551
01:03:20,154 --> 01:03:23,772
Get 'em in their stand.

552
01:04:14,603 --> 01:04:17,387
Bilbo.
-No.

553
01:04:17,554 --> 01:04:22,520
Lay down your arms,
or we will rip his off.

554
01:04:38,541 --> 01:04:40,577
Don't bother cooking 'em?

555
01:04:40,744 --> 01:04:44,899
Let's just sit on him
and squas him into jelly.

556
01:04:45,063 --> 01:04:49,721
They must be sautd and grilled
with a sprigkle of Sage.

557
01:04:49,885 --> 01:04:52,961
That does sound quite nice.

558
01:04:56,203 --> 01:05:00,192
Never mind the seasoning.
We ain't got all night.

559
01:05:00,361 --> 01:05:06,587
Dawn ain't far away, let's get a move on.
I don't fancy being turned to stone.

560
01:05:08,921 --> 01:05:13,412
Wait, you are making a terrible mistake!

561
01:05:13,576 --> 01:05:17,979
You can't reason with them. They are half-wits.
-Half-wits? What does that make us?

562
01:05:18,147 --> 01:05:21,391
I meant with the...seasoning.

563
01:05:21,556 --> 01:05:26,009
What about the seasoning?
-Well, Have you smelled them?

564
01:05:26,044 --> 01:05:30,043
You're gonna need something stronger than Sage
before you plate this one up.

565
01:05:30,044 --> 01:05:33,963
Traitor.
-What do you know about cooking dwarfs?

566
01:05:33,999 --> 01:05:38,913
Shut up.
Let the flagger burglar hobbit talk.

567
01:05:39,078 --> 01:05:43,860
The secret to cooking dwarfs...

568
01:05:44,025 --> 01:05:48,437
C'mon...
-The secret is ...

569
01:05:50,674 --> 01:05:54,789
To skin them first.

570
01:05:54,956 --> 01:05:59,151
Tom, get me filleting knife.
-I will get you for this...

571
01:05:59,319 --> 01:06:03,641
I won't forget that.
-What a lot of rubbish.

572
01:06:03,810 --> 01:06:09,209
I've eaten plenty wood man with skins on.
Scoffer marks with boots and all.

573
01:06:10,167 --> 01:06:14,946
He is right.
There is nothing wrong with bit of raw dwarfs.

574
01:06:17,482 --> 01:06:22,940
Nice and crunchy.
-Not that one. He is infected.

575
01:06:23,676 --> 01:06:28,870
He what?
-He's got worms, in his tubes.

576
01:06:31,238 --> 01:06:35,604
In fact, they all have. They're infested with parasites.
It's a terrible business.

577
01:06:35,769 --> 01:06:40,508
I would don't risk it. I really wouldn't.
-Parasites...did he said parasites?

578
01:06:40,672 --> 01:06:44,289
We have no parasites.

579
01:06:55,469 --> 01:06:58,338
We are riddled.

580
01:06:58,501 --> 01:07:01,454
What would you have us do then?

581
01:07:01,618 --> 01:07:06,774
Let them all go?
You think i don't know what you're upto?

582
01:07:06,937 --> 01:07:11,344
These little ferret
Is taking us for a fool.

583
01:07:11,513 --> 01:07:13,413
Ferrets?
-Fools?

584
01:07:13,424 --> 01:07:16,952
The dawn will take you all!

585
01:07:17,867 --> 01:07:21,383
Who is that?
-No idea, can we eat him too?

586
01:07:47,192 --> 01:07:49,816
Get your foot out of my mouth.

587
01:07:58,958 --> 01:08:03,444
Where did you go to, if i may ask?
-to look ahead.

588
01:08:03,613 --> 01:08:07,395
What brought you back?
-Looking behind.

589
01:08:07,563 --> 01:08:11,152
Nasty business.
-Still they're all in one piece.

590
01:08:11,153 --> 01:08:12,857
No thanks to your burgler.

591
01:08:14,393 --> 01:08:16,745
He had to mask.
To bade for time.

592
01:08:21,791 --> 01:08:24,561
They must've come down from Etinwoods.

593
01:08:24,595 --> 01:08:27,082
Since when did the mountain trolls
venture down far South?

594
01:08:27,083 --> 01:08:29,973
They have not ages.

595
01:08:30,632 --> 01:08:34,498
Not since the darker power
ruled this land.

596
01:08:39,033 --> 01:08:43,517
They couldn't have moved in daylight.

597
01:08:43,552 --> 01:08:48,001
There must be a cave nearby.

598
01:08:57,199 --> 01:09:02,374
What a stench.
-It's a trollenhol.

599
01:09:02,409 --> 01:09:07,549
Be careful what you touch.

600
01:09:18,026 --> 01:09:21,102
Seems ashame, just to let 'em lay around.

601
01:09:21,612 --> 01:09:26,962
Anyone could take it.
-Agreed. Nori.

602
01:09:26,998 --> 01:09:29,635
Get a shovel.

603
01:09:45,302 --> 01:09:48,379
This sword are not made by any troll.

604
01:09:53,326 --> 01:09:57,772
Nor they're made by smiths among men.

605
01:10:02,342 --> 01:10:07,994
These are forged in Gondorlet,
by the High Elves in the first age.

606
01:10:08,119 --> 01:10:13,022
You could not wish for a finer blade.

607
01:10:37,129 --> 01:10:43,167
We are making a long term deposit.
-Let's get out of this foul place.

608
01:10:43,269 --> 01:10:46,839
Come on, let's go.

609
01:11:09,944 --> 01:11:13,400
Here. This is about your size.

610
01:11:19,009 --> 01:11:23,656
I can't take this.
-The blade is of Elves make.

611
01:11:23,690 --> 01:11:28,867
Which means, It glow blue
when Orcs and Goblins are near by.

612
01:11:29,813 --> 01:11:34,135
I've never used a sword in my life.
-And hope you never have to.

613
01:11:34,171 --> 01:11:37,752
But if you do, remember this:

614
01:11:37,918 --> 01:11:42,575
<i>True courage is about knowing
when not to take a life ...</i>

615
01:11:43,317 --> 01:11:47,073
<i>but when to spare one.</i>

616
01:11:50,843 --> 01:11:55,406
Something's coming!
-Stay together.

617
01:11:55,441 --> 01:11:59,953
Hurry there.
Arm you.

618
01:12:16,671 --> 01:12:21,518
Thieves. Fire.
Murder.

619
01:12:21,681 --> 01:12:24,125
Radagast.

620
01:12:24,671 --> 01:12:28,156
Radagast the Brown.

621
01:12:30,839 --> 01:12:35,828
What on earth are you doing here?
-I was looking for you, Gandalf. Something's wrong.

622
01:12:35,997 --> 01:12:39,479
Something's...terribly wrong.
-Yes?

623
01:12:44,112 --> 01:12:50,176
Just give me a minute.
Oh, I had a thought, now i've lost it.

624
01:12:50,342 --> 01:12:54,914
It's right there, on the tip of my tongue.

625
01:12:55,084 --> 01:12:59,988
It's not a thought all.
It is a little ...

626
01:13:00,577 --> 01:13:03,679
Stick Insect.

627
01:13:05,866 --> 01:13:11,778
The Green Wood is sick, Gandalf.
A darkness has fallen over it.

628
01:13:12,473 --> 01:13:17,005
Nothing grows anymore,
at least nothing good.

629
01:13:17,171 --> 01:13:21,899
The air is foul decay,
but the worst are the webs.

630
01:13:22,229 --> 01:13:25,907
Webs? What do you mean?
-Spiders, Gandalf.

631
01:13:25,943 --> 01:13:30,929
Giant ones.
Some kind of spawn of... Ungoliant.

632
01:13:30,930 --> 01:13:33,274
But, I'm not a wizard.

633
01:13:33,309 --> 01:13:38,414
I followed their trail...
They came from Dol Guldur.

634
01:13:40,520 --> 01:13:46,688
Dol Guldur?
But the old fort is abandoned?

635
01:13:46,742 --> 01:13:50,390
No, Gandalf.

636
01:13:50,555 --> 01:13:52,767
It is not.

637
01:14:00,287 --> 01:14:07,104
A dark power dwells in there.
Such that I've never felt before.

638
01:14:08,435 --> 01:14:13,485
It is the shadow of an ancient horror.

639
01:14:18,816 --> 01:14:24,098
One that can summon the spirits...
of the dead.

640
01:14:40,746 --> 01:14:42,590
I saw him, Gandalf.

641
01:14:44,027 --> 01:14:49,491
Out of the darkness...
A Necromancer has come.

642
01:14:58,328 --> 01:15:00,952
Quickly.

643
01:15:02,989 --> 01:15:04,986
Wait for me.

644
01:15:17,906 --> 01:15:21,806
Sorry.
-Try this low tribute.

645
01:15:21,904 --> 01:15:24,320
It helps settle the nerves.

646
01:15:27,081 --> 01:15:29,456
Breathe out.

647
01:15:35,852 --> 01:15:40,339
Now... A necromancer?
Are you sure?

648
01:15:53,585 --> 01:15:59,056
That is not from the world of the living.

649
01:16:05,213 --> 01:16:11,017
Was that a wolf? Are wolves out there?
-Wolfs, No, that is not a wolf.

650
01:16:26,635 --> 01:16:29,827
Wargs Orcs. Which means Orc pack is not
far behind.

651
01:16:29,889 --> 01:16:31,401
Orc Pack?

652
01:16:31,454 --> 01:16:34,374
Who did you tell about your quest,
beyond your kin?

653
01:16:34,375 --> 01:16:35,375
-No one.

654
01:16:35,198 --> 01:16:38,134
Who did you tell?
-No one, I swear.

655
01:16:38,722 --> 01:16:42,587
What in the name of Durin is going on?
-We are being hunted.

656
01:16:42,909 --> 01:16:44,619
We have to get out of here.

657
01:16:44,620 --> 01:16:48,213
We can't, we have no ponies.
They bolted.

658
01:16:48,573 --> 01:16:50,345
I'll draw them off.

659
01:16:50,447 --> 01:16:53,495
These are Gundabad-Wargs.
They'll out run you.

660
01:16:53,602 --> 01:16:59,050
These are Rhosgobel rabbits.
I would like to see them try.

661
01:17:10,901 --> 01:17:13,230
Come and get me.

662
01:17:22,545 --> 01:17:24,064
Come on.

663
01:17:51,901 --> 01:17:53,625
Stay together.

664
01:18:05,460 --> 01:18:07,912
Ori, No. Go back.

665
01:18:10,871 --> 01:18:13,245
Come on, quick.

666
01:18:15,034 --> 01:18:17,175
Where are you leading us?

667
01:19:26,133 --> 01:19:28,710
Move...
-Run!!!!

668
01:19:45,303 --> 01:19:47,931
There they are.

669
01:19:48,455 --> 01:19:51,261
This way.
Quickly.

670
01:20:02,213 --> 01:20:07,513
There is more coming.
-Kili?

671
01:20:11,543 --> 01:20:14,055
We are surrounded.

672
01:20:17,344 --> 01:20:20,870
Where is Gandalf?
-He has abandoned us.

673
01:20:27,240 --> 01:20:30,212
Hold your ground.

674
01:20:36,250 --> 01:20:38,017
Kili.

675
01:20:38,566 --> 01:20:42,621
This way you fools.
-Come on, move.

676
01:20:44,495 --> 01:20:47,700
Quickly, all of you.

677
01:20:48,440 --> 01:20:51,180
Go..go...go.

678
01:21:01,226 --> 01:21:02,897
Nine, ten ...

679
01:21:04,513 --> 01:21:06,510
Kili.

680
01:21:45,768 --> 01:21:47,696
Elves.

681
01:21:50,563 --> 01:21:54,302
I can't see where the path leads.
Do we follow it or not?

682
01:21:54,342 --> 01:21:55,987
Follow, of course.

683
01:21:59,605 --> 01:22:01,769
I think that would be wise.

